(1) East 115th Street, west from the Harlem River, and showing clearance of the former plant of the Standard Gas Light Co. Notice gas tanks at the S.E. corner of Pleasant Ave. The row of buildings on the right, are on the east side of Pleasant Ave., between 115th and 116th Streets. September 12, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, from a different angle. Building shown on the extreme right, is a plant of the N.Y. Ice Co., and fronts onto East 116th Street. September 12, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same as No. 2, at a later date. November 9, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

East 115th Street, west from the Harlem River. On the left appears a portion of the Standard Gas Light Co Plant, in the process of demolition.

July 12, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)
East 115th Street, south side, west from, but not including the Harlem River, to and including Pleasant Ave. Buildings and tanks shown; a portion of the Standard Gas Light Co. Plant, are being completely demolished.
July 16, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same; from a point still further eastward.
July 16, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)
East 115th Street, north side, west from (No. 515), and the Harlem River. The view shows the demolition of buildings on this block; formerly a portion of the Standard Gas Light Co., Plant.

July 16, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same; slightly westward. Spire shown is the tower of the Church of Our Lady of Mt. Carmel, west of Pleasant Ave.

September 12, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
